{"questionId":"3097264","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Kepler then considered a non-cylindrical barrel whose base and lid are circles with radius <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math> and whose length is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>He modelled the curved surface of this barrel by rotating a quadratic curve, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ASB</mi></math>, with equation <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn></math>, about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis. The origin of the coordinate system is at the centre of one of the circular faces as shown in the following diagram. <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math> is at the vertex of the quadratic curve and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>SD</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/15f49f7264e76d06bf3abae8553d5ed9c0944876.png\"></p>\n<p>Kepler wished to find out if his barrel would give him more wine than any cylindrical barrel with <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>d</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>6</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math> respectively.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the quadratic curve, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ASB</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-coordinate of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">S</mi></math> is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>let the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-coordinate be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></msub></math></p>\n<p>attempt at Pythagoras&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>6</mn><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><msup><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></msup></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><msub><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow><mo>=</mo><msqrt><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>247</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>247213</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> The <em><strong>(M1)</strong> </em>mark can be implied by a <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math>-coordinate of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>447</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>647</mn></math> seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>any valid method to find equation <br>e.g. quadratic regression, vertex form, simultaneous equation.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award only if the student has found three points on the curve.</p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>295</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>236</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>295081</mn><mo>…</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>236065</mn><mo>…</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> if one coefficient (<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>295081</mn><mo>…</mo></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>236065</mn><mo>…</mo></math>) is correct or if “<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo></math>” is missing, <em><strong>A2</strong></em> for completely correct equation.<br>Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>294</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>235</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>2</mn></math> obtained from using the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> sf value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>y</mi><mi>s</mi></msub></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>295</mn><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>247</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <em><strong>A2</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>295081</mn><mo>…</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>247213</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>295</mn></math>, <em><strong>A2</strong> </em>for completely correct equation.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3097264","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ1.1f","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the quadratic curve, ASB.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"f","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.13—Non-linear regression","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.8—Use of technology to solve systems of linear equations and polynomial equations"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}